---
import Icon from "./Icon.astro";
---

<section class="mt-4 mb-4" id="discipline">
  <div class="bento-card rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-16 relative overflow-hidden">
    <!-- Background Decoration -->
    <div
      class="absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none opacity-[0.03]"
      style="background-image: linear-gradient(#fff 1px, transparent 1px), linear-gradient(90deg, #fff 1px, transparent 1px); background-size: 40px 40px;"
    >
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-12 items-start relative z-10">
      <div class="flex-1">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
          <Icon name="precision_manufacturing" size={24} class="text-primary" />
          <h2
            class="text-xl font-bold font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-white"
          >
            The Product Mindset
          </h2>
        </div>
        <h3
          class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white leading-tight mb-6"
        >
          Engineering for Velocity.
        </h3>
      </div>
      <div
        class="flex-1 border-l border-surface-border pl-0 lg:pl-10 pt-4 lg:pt-0"
      >
        <p
          class="font-mono text-sm md:text-base text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-6"
        >
          I believe that code is a means to an end, not the end itself. My
          workflow is built around efficiency: leveraging AI to handle
          boilerplate, so I can focus on architecture, user experience, and
          shipping value. Whether it's a startup MVP or a high-load commercial
          project, my goal is to deliver excellence without the overhead.
        </p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div>
            <p class="text-xs text-text-dim font-mono mb-1">Constraint</p>
            <p class="text-white font-bold">Time-to-Market &lt; 1 week</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-xs text-text-dim font-mono mb-1">Goal</p>
            <p class="text-white font-bold">High Conversion UX</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
